The paper deals with detecting fake users in online social networks, which is a problem related to social network analysis and cybersecurity. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CYBER (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations of existing approaches, which is related to the social and ethical implications of cybersecurity, making cs.SOC (Computers and Society) a possible sub-category as well.
